# okonkwobit

Okonkwobit smart contract project managed with Clarinet.

## Overview
- Contract: `contracts/okonkwobit.clar`
- Token: fungible token `okonkwobit`
- Public functions:
  - `mint (amount uint, recipient principal)` — owner-only mint
  - `transfer (amount uint, sender principal, recipient principal)` — standard transfer
  - `set-owner (new-owner principal)` — change owner (owner-only)
- Read-only:
  - `get-owner () -> principal`
  - `get-balance (who principal) -> uint`
  - `get-total-supply () -> uint`

## Install Clarinet
- `npm i -g @hirosystems/clarinet`
- Verify: `clarinet --version`

## Usage
- Typecheck/compile: `clarinet check`
- REPL: `clarinet console`
  - Example calls (from console):
    - `(contract-call? .okonkwobit mint u1000 '<recipient-principal>)`
    - `(contract-call? .okonkwobit transfer u250 '<sender-principal> '<recipient-principal>)`
    - `(contract-call? .okonkwobit set-owner '<new-owner-principal>)`
  - Unauthorized actions return `(err u403)`

## Testing
- Install deps: `npm install`
- Run tests: `npm test`
- Watch: `npm run test:watch`

## Project structure
- `contracts/` — Clarity contracts (main: `okonkwobit.clar`)
- `tests/` — TypeScript tests with `vitest`
- `settings/` — devnet/testnet/mainnet configs
- `Clarinet.toml` — project and contract registration

